               <msContents class="lemmatic">
                  <summary>This manuscript contains commentary on the book of Aphorisms attributed to <persName type="standard" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/287984736" key="person_287984736">Hippocrates</persName>.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Or_58-item1">
                     <author key="person_f4896">
                        <persName type="supplied" subtype="aut">ʾIbrāhīm al-Kīshīإبراهيم الكيشي</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_7762">وسائل الوصول إلى مسائل الفصول</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc" key="work_7762">Means to Arrive at the Questions about the Aphorisms</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="alt" key="work_7762">Wasāʼl al-Wuṣūl ilā Masāʼil al-Fuṣūl</title>
                     <note>Original manuscript in Leiden University Library.</note>
                     <note>
                        <p>Since it is a gloss, it is not clear whether it contains all of <persName key="person_f4508">al-Kīshī</persName> ’s text. The aphorisms are not cited verbatim, and commentaries on several aphorisms are omitted.</p>
                        <p>The copy is wrongly labeled as a commentary by <persName type="supplied" key="person_f4507">al-Kīlānī</persName> on the title page. This is a collection of <persName type="supplied" key="person_f5647">‘Abd al-Raḥmān al-Ṭabīb</persName> ’s glosses (ḥawāshi) on <persName type="supplied" key="person_f5685">‘Izz al-Dīn Ibrāhīm al-Kīshī</persName> ’s commentary on the Aphorisms. The introduction begins on <locus>f. 1b</locus>; the beginning of each Book is as follows: Bk1: 1b; Bk2: 9b; Bk3: 22a; Bk4: 32a; Bk5: 41a; Bk6: 48a; Bk7: 54b.</p>
                     </note>
                     <respStmt>
                        <persName type="supplied" subtype="commentator" key="person_f4918">ʿAbd al-Raḥīm al-Ṭabīb’عبد الرحيم الطبيب</persName>
                        <resp><!--Required resp added in conversion -JC --></resp>
